
[1]pastil

   PAS'TIL, n. [L. pastillus.]

   1. A roll of paste, or a kind of paste made of different colors ground
   with gum-water in order to make crayons.

   2. In pharmacy, a dry composition of sweet smelling resins, aromatic
   woods, &c. burnt to clear and scent the air of a room.
